reviews.review_text: GDTRFB admittedly biased, i am a flat out fool for that tune...this is one of the best---ever.
Fantastic listened to this quite a bit recently, great show.

This setlist is the best... ever? Starting out with an amazing Sugaree, Cassidy, then some other classics, even Row Jimmy followed by Scarlet-Fire?!

Then starting out set 2 with Estimated, Bertha, The Music Never Stopped, this show could end here and it would still be amazing but then they bust out a short and sweet Help-Slip-Franklin's, followed by some other staples including a top version of GDTRFB?! THIS IS AMAZING.

Jimmy Warburton tape.   If our memory is correct Jimmy did this. From 60 ft out center  grandads cane and ecm 99a stereo mic... thanks for  patches from Jerry Moore's effort. see Springfield 6-30-74 for setup caricature.
